{{Orphan|date=April 2014}} {{Infobox journal | title = Research and Humanities in Medical Education | cover = | editor = Upreet Dhaliwal | discipline = [[Humanities]] in [[medical education]] | abbreviation = Res. Humanit. Med. Educ. | publisher = Medical Humanities Group at the [[University College of Medical Sciences]] and [[Guru Teg Bahadur Hospital]] | country = India | frequency = | openaccess = Yes | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.rhime.in | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = http://www.rhime.in/archives.aspx | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = | eISSN = }} ''''' Research and Humanities in Medical Education ''''' (RHiME)is an [[open-access]] [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by the Medical Humanities Group at the [[University College of Medical Sciences]] and [[Guru Teg Bahadur Hospital]], Delhi. It covers the role of the [[humanities]] in [[medical education]], including the [[history of medicine]], [[narrative medicine]], [[graphic medicine]], [[disability studies]], and arts-based interventions, such as healing by means of [[Theatre of the Oppressed]], poetry, literature, film, music and art.<ref>{{cite news |title=UCMS launches online scientific journal on Medical Humanities |url=http://www.indiamedicaltimes.com/2014/04/16/ucms-launches-online-scientific-journal-on-medical-humanities/ |newspaper=India Medical Times |date=16 April 2014}}</ref> The journal was established in 2014.<ref>{{cite news |title=Doctors for humanities |url=http://www.educationtimes.com/article/248/2014041420140414154107265ba9bf2f/Doctors-for-humanities-.html |newspaper=Education Times |date=14 April 2014}}</ref> The [[editor-in-chief]] is Upreet Dhaliwal.
