{{Infobox person | name = Šefik Bešlagić | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1908|04|06|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Tuzla]], [[Condominium of Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[Austria-Hungary]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1990|11|19|1908|04|06|df=y}} | death_place = [[Sarajevo]], [[SR Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[SFR Yugoslavia]] | nationality = Austro-Hungarian, Yugoslav | other_names = | known_for = Bosnian history | occupation = Historian }}
'''Šefik Bešlagić''' (6 April 1908 – 19 November 1990) was a cultural historian from [[Bosnia]]. From 1953 to 1967 Šefik Bešlagić was the director of the Institute for the Protection of Cultural Monuments of [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. He explored the medieval necropolis of marble or ''[[Stećci]]''. He was a historian of material culture, especially of stones (''[[Stećci]]'', ''nišani'', ''čatrnje'', ''stolice'').
== Biography == Bešlagić was born in the town of Gornja [[Tuzla]] in 1908.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://novovrijeme.ba/efik-beslagic-epitaf-neumornom-istrazivacu/|title=Šefik Bešlagić: Epitaf neumornom istraživaču|publisher=Novo vrijeme|date=20 May 2014|accessdate=1 June 2014}}</ref> His mother Devleta (née Mulalić) was a housewife, while his father Agan was a teacher.
Šefik Bešlagić was educated in Tuzla, [[Doboj]] and [[Sarajevo]], before teaching in [[Derventa]] and [[Gračanica, Bosnia and Herzegovina|Gračanica]].<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=https://www.academia.edu/3560504/Bibliografija_radova_Sefika_Beslagica_1908-1990_djelo_posveceno_izucavanju_materijalne_kulture_Hercegovina_15-16_Mostar_2003|title=Bibliografija radova Šefika Bešlagića|publisher=Academia|year=2003|accessdate=1 June 2014}}</ref>
